verbose_text: The daily use of oral estrogens is considered to worsen urinary incontinence; however, its pathophysiology remains unknown.9 Antidepressants, antipsychotics, and benzodiazepines drugs, which impact on the central nervous system, have also been shown to trigger the development of OAB.10, 11 Their effects might result from relaxing the pelvic floor muscles, interference with afferent nerve pathways from the bladder, or from indirectly leading to an inability to toilet.
